  "read": "B-M ordering holds across cohorts but the frequency-attributable premium is only the below_static-vs-below_active gap (~5%); adopter/above premia are positioning, not commitment. Congestion pricing is infeasible for ~94% of pairs (they never reprice) and at most weak among active undercutters; rationing intensity is inversely ordered in repricing flexibility \u2014 the menu-rigidity mechanism at cohort level.",
